tweets.text:
Here's some good news today: our new river channel in the heart of #StokeOnTrent is complete! We've changed the course of the Trent, making it so much better for wildlife &amp; people. 
See full film: https://t.co/lSdaVprgRX
@EnvAgencyMids @SoTCityCouncil @CraigBennett3 @JamesBevanEA https://t.co/4IKmIfsHEs

What's going on at Day's Lock?
@EnvAgencySE is repairing the lock's chambers and replacing tailgates. The first lock here was built in 1789; the current one in 1925. It's the main gauging station for measuring the water flow in the River Thames (source Wiki).
